2 R'(t)=r(t) R(t)
\dfrac{R''}{R} = \dfrac{r^2}{4} + \dfrac{r'}{2}
R?
\frac{R''}{R}=\frac{R''}{R'}\frac{R'}{R}=(\ln \left(R'\right))'r/2\\ \Rightarrow (\ln (R'))'r/2=r/2+r'/2\\ \Rightarrow (\ln (R'))'=1+\frac{r'}{r}=1+(\ln(r))'\quad(\mbox{Assuming}\ r\ne 0)\\ \Rightarrow \ln R'=t+\ln r+A\Rightarrow R'/r=ae^t\\ \Rightarrow R/2=ae^t\Rightarrow R=2ae^t
